   design practice. In this paper, we examine whether this model can be
   used as a predictive model. This is done by testing its predictive
   capacity for the design behaviour of students that are formally taught
   design and design methods. The behavioural observations used in this
   study are based on protocols of 15 design sessions involving mechanical
   engineering students after their first year of design education and 31
   design sessions of the students using various concept generation
   methods. The design protocols and the Systematic Approach are coded
   uniformly using the Function-Behaviour-Structure (FBS) design issue
   schema. Cumulative occurrence analysis is used to derive qualitative and
